I've been to this location twice. Once for my coworker, once for myself. Both times I wanted to try the cheesecake sundae. Both times they were out of ice cream. How are you out of ice cream at 11:20am and you just opened at 10am? I got the big buford combo. I was so disappointed. Not only is the burger small, too expensive for the size of it, and tasted like straight salt, but the fries tasted like funnel cake, I'm sure from shared grease with the funnel fries. I threw my lunch away. I should've went to BK. Oh. And there were a total of 3 cars in the drive thru. It took me 20 minutes to order my food, pay for it and receive it. This is not fast food.

I wish I can give zero Stars! I went to buy chicken sandwich meals for my family and when we bit into them they were RAW! RAWWWWWW! Like someone dipped them in grease and pulled them right back out! I called the manager IMMEDIATELY he said to return to the restaurant and he will give us our refund. (So now i have to be inconvenience by using gas from my car and we still haven't eaten)  When we got there he looked at the sandwiches and saw that the meat was raw. Went to the register and gave us $4. I asked him where is my full refund? He said it's OUR POLICY to only give you a refund for what you bring back! So you telling me instead of apologizing and begging for forgiveness and giving me a FULL REFUND to show remorse...you give me $4 to cover what i brought back to you. . He then says well if you want a full refund I need to call the GM. I SAID CALL HIM! I assume the GM got him straight because he came back with a bs apology and my FULL refund! This is the WORSE restaurant everrrrr! Sad and pathetic!
